        <profileDesc>
            <abstract>
                A brief letter thanking Hardy for his reply and for his willingness to write
                a short story as Fawcett had requested. She hopes to see him in London and
                share stories that motivated her work helping vulnerable girls.
            </abstract>
            
            <handDesc>
                <handNote>Brown ink, cursive; steady hand with occasional ligatures and long descenders.</handNote>
            </handDesc>
            
            <note type="context">
                Millicent Garrett Fawcett, a prominent suffragist and reformer, corresponded
                with Thomas Hardy on matters related to social purity, literature, and women’s welfare.
            </note>
