            <head>
                <persName ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/73880180/">Millicent Garrett Fawcett</persName>
            </head>
            
            <dateline>
                <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2634308/">Rustington, Worthing</placeName>;<lb/>
                (<placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2643743/">London</placeName> address: 2 Gower Street, London)<lb/>
                <date when="1892-04-24">April 24.</date>
            </dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Mr Hardy,</salute>
            
            <p>
                I thank you very sincerely for your letter.<lb/>
                I am not without hope you will write a short story on the lines I have
                endeavoured to indicate.<lb/>
                So few people could do it; but you can.<lb/>
                You and Mrs Hardy will lose no time when you are in<lb/>
            </p>
            
            <!-- PAGE 3 (recto of second leaf) -->
            <pb facs="uoedh_hl_h.2359_3.jpg"/>
            
            <p>
                London. I should be very delighted to see you; and I could perhaps tell you
                some of the true stories that moved me first to wish you to beg your help in this.<lb/>
            </p>
            
            <closer>
                Yours very truly,<lb/>
                <signed>
                    <persName ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/73880180/">M. Fawcett</persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
            
